Questions that arise after the accident: Are the stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the Student Agency bus near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel within the bus during the journey.
"If we wanted to respect the law strictly and formally, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," says the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the bus path.
At that time, unfortunately, the girl was sitting next to the driver in the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had at her disposal two other seats.
The coach may have an accident, or even a sudden brake, also when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is by virtue of its data sheet equipped with standing seats or not.
If this standing equipment is not approved, the passengers shall remain seated.
Student Agency long distance buses do not have standing seats; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the company manager Radim Jančura.
"This is an issue that we have dealt with with the department and, at the beginning, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got that passengers can go to the washroom during the ride provided they have their own seat, "he unveiled his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no unambiguous legal interpretation of the role of steward - there is no legal requirement for that role.
On the other hand, there are also no legal provisions prohibiting the carrier from offering services.
The Road Transport Act only knows the term "vehicle receiver"; it does not define its rights and duties, "added spokesperson Hanzelka with more ambiguity.
Josef Pokorný, the director of the road traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law sufficiently addresses the problem.
"It all depends on whether the coach has in its approval permission to offer standing seats.
It's all in there, "he says.
Buses are divided into urban, with standing seats and limited maximum speed, intercity seats and higher authorized speed, and long distance buses without standing seats with the highest authorized maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Hořín, an expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"On regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
Neither is it safe when turbulence occurs and the air hostess can hit her head. "
"However, in the event that the bus has suddenly slowed down, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
Same way as in an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards by internal requirements, "he says, and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not resolved.
Jančura is ready to delete these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer the services of stewards.
He hires two hundred of them.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their occupation to be a risky one.
"Nevertheless, as soon as I feel that this is a risky trade, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper at boarding.
It would also reduce costs, "he says.
The concern for safety is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of Asiana Alexei Litvine, which ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We have no hostesses. We have been opposed to this from the beginning.
Sooner or later this will end in a fatal accident, "he said a year ago in Týden.cz.
An immense tragedy has come
A young hostess from the Plzeo region, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably tied up the emergency stop strip without using a flashing light and blocked the way to the bus.
The latter's driver tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he approached it by his right side.
Jančura refuses to allow the two seats reserved for the Stewards to be sold.
"In the case of long distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but as regards financial compensation, it also relies on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been being drafted for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide details of the movement of stewards on the bus.
"However, it did not lead to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the motorway and the use of the mobile at the wheel, "says the expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not regard the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger passenger safety," concluded spokesperson Hanzelka, stating that the control of bus safety is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
