"The Commission is absolutely independent; all political, social and cultural ideas are represented in it - stresses Alemanno - it will have to propose ideas for the development of Rome to be used by political decision-makers, who remain the Committee and the Communal Council.
No superposition of roles, but only the desire to have a place where to draw up a great project for Rome.
In March, she will have completed her tasks and will then disappear, as this experiment must have a precise time span.
In June - announced on May- we will present the strategic plan resulting from the work carried out by the Commission for the future of Rome Capital. "
