We, on the contrary, want to see forward, and further, towards a deeper foresight, working seriously for the development of Rome and its future. "
Moreover, the Mayor of Rome would like to stress that "this Commission is not an unnecessary body or a bureaucratic body: it is absolutely free, and will not cost the Roman citadines a euro, and will serve to study and involve the best intelligences that express the capital.
